02/05/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski opened the first SOS-Kinder village in Macedonia on Friday (29 April). The president of SOS-Kinderdorf International, Helmut Kutin, accompanied him. The village comprises ten houses and will host 59 children -- 37 Macedonians, 16 Romas, 5 Albanians and 1 Bosniak. The total capacity of the facility is 84 people. (Vest, Dnevnik - 30/04/05; A1 - 29/04/05)
